\fs28 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}Step 1: The API Wrapper (FastAPI)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\fs22 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}"Before deploying, I had to make the model usable by others."\
{\listtext	\'95	}Instead of just having a .pt file (the YOLO model), you wrapped it in a REST API using FastAPI.\
\pard\tx105\tx825\pardeftab720\li825\fi-360\ri0\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 Why FastAPI? It is faster than Flask, supports asynchronous processing (handling multiple factory cameras at once), and automatically generates documentation.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 The Logic: You created a /predict endpoint that takes an image, runs inference, and returns a JSON decision (PASS / REJECT).\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs28 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}Step 2: Containerization (Docker)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs22 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}"I containerized the application to solve the 'it works on my machine' problem."\
{\listtext	\'95	}You created a Dockerfile which is a recipe for building the computer that runs your code.\
\pard\tx105\tx825\pardeftab720\li825\fi-360\ri0\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
