\ls5\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 Cross-Platform Build: Since you developed on a Mac (ARM architecture) but deployed to Azure (Linux/AMD64), you used the flag --platform linux/amd64 during the build.\
\ls5\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 Push: You used docker push to upload the versioned image (v1) to your private Azure Registry.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\fs28 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}Step 5: Deployment (Azure Container Instances)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\fs22 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}"I deployed the model as a Serverless Container."\
{\listtext	\'95	}You chose ACI (Azure Container Instances) for the deployment.\
\pard\tx105\tx825\pardeftab720\li825\fi-360\ri0\sl276\slmult1\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 Why ACI? It is "Serverless Containers." You didn't need to manage a Virtual Machine (VM) or a complex Kubernetes cluster. It spins up in seconds and you only pay for the seconds it runs.\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 Configuration: You allocated 1 CPU and 2GB RAM, sufficient for the YOLO nano/small model.\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}\uc0\u9679 
\f0 	\cf2 Security: You injected environment variables (API_KEY) at runtime so secrets weren't hardcoded in the script.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\sb240\sa120\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
